Porphyrion has here the name ‘Fuscum’ (or, as it appears in Ascensius’ text twice over, ‘ Tuscum')‚ 01111 says he was a distin- guished writer of tragedies. Here he is associated with Varius, and in the latter of the above passages a Viscus also appears in Varius’ company. In the former there are two Visci and a Fuscus, and Varius just above.
